Hello Marco,

In spite of what the javadoc says, version 1.1 of the commons-cli library supports retrieving options by their long names. The maven build config in commons/pom.xml calls for commons-cli 1.1.

Is it possible that you have your classpath configured in eclipse to point to commons-cli 1.0?

Noah


Marco Fabbri wrote:
&gt; Hello,
&gt; I am trying to integrate Heritrix in a new project.
&gt; I chose Heritrix2 because of the new redesign.
&gt; First I tried version 2.0.2, but
&gt; http://webarchive.jira.com/browse/HER-1576 blocks a feature that I
&gt; need (max-bytes-download).
&gt; So I did checkout from SVN, but then I encountered a problem at startup.
&gt; Running inside Eclipse with the following startup params:
&gt; 
&gt; -p 8999 -a xxxx
&gt; 
&gt; the program exits with the following message:
&gt; 
&gt; Unless --no-web-ui is specified, you must specify an admin password
&gt; for the web UI using --webui-admin.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Debugging the code I noticed that inside the main method all hasOption
&gt; control parameters have been substituted with the long names (e.g.
&gt; line 223
&gt; 
&gt;   if (cl.hasOption(&#39;h&#39;)) {
&gt; 
&gt; has become
&gt; 
&gt;  if (cl.hasOption(&quot;help&quot;)) {
&gt; 
&gt; IMO this is not correct as hasOption param should be the short name as
&gt; stated in the javadoc
&gt; http://commons.apache.org/cli/apidocs/org/apache/commons/cli/CommandLine.html#hasOption(java.lang.String)
&gt; 
&gt; Going back to short names the program works correctly.
&gt; 
&gt; Do you also think this is a bug?
&gt; If so, unless you are planning to fix it soon I&#39;ll be happy to submit a patch.
&gt; 
&gt; Thank you for your attention and for your project which is great!
&gt; 
&gt; Marco
